pageContext.claim: ““Mueller was asked whether or not the investigation was impeded in any way, and he said no.” In other words, there was NO OBSTRUCTION. @KatiePavlich @FoxNews”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is wrong here. Mueller saying the investigation was not impeded does not mean there were not attempts (though failed) to obstruct justice, which could be considered criminal offenses. The Mueller report did not say one way or another that the president did or did not attempt to obstruct justice.
